    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-04T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-04T09:00:00-05:00" n="854"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d854">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.006/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-04T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 4, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 4—1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Complete control over exchange and imports, exports instituted effective
                    December 3. Merchandise already in transit or for which special permits
                    previously issued may proceed but all other must obtain import authorization and
                    exchange permits. Foreign currency proceeds of exports and all other
                    transactions must be surrendered to Exchange Bureau. Banque de Syrie Liban
                    acting as official exchange agents. Compagnie Algérienne and Crédit Foncier
                    d’Algérie Tunisie also authorized. Products from France or territories exempted.
                    Airmail report follows.<note n="40" xml:id="d854fn40">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Palmer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
